abstract: LAKE PLACID, N.Y., Dec. 16 Taffy Pergament of the Westchester Figure Skating Club held a slight lead over Honey Kerr of the Skating Club of New York today in the senior women's event at the North Atlantic championships at the Olympic Arena.
headline_main: Taffy Pergament Leading In Skating at Lake Placid
headline_print_headline: Taffy Pergament Leading In Skating at Lake Placid

abstract: LAKE PLACID, N.Y., Dec. 15 --A pair of 11-year-old Livingston, N.J., girls were among the winners today as the North Atlantic figure-skating championships started at the Olympic Arena.
headline_main: Two Jersey Girls, 11, Take Skate Titles at Lake Placid
headline_print_headline: Two Jersey Girls, 11, Take Skate Titles at Lake Placid
byline_original: Special to The New York Times

abstract: WESTBURY, L.I., Dec. 13 One player, out of the 11,303 who attended, found out that it was worthwhile to brave the snow to play the twin double at Roosevelt Raceway tonight. This player, who asked to remain anonymous, collected $9,083.20 for $2 as the only one whose ticket was "alive" for the big payoff.
headline_main: TROT TWIN DOUBLE RETURNS $9,083; Payoff Goes to One Bettor, Even Though He Loses 9th
headline_print_headline: TROT TWIN DOUBLE RETURNS $9,083; Payoff Goes to One Bettor, Even Though He Loses 9th
byline_original: By Joe Nichols Special To the New Yok Times
